The paper deals with the problem of determining the aesthetic quality of graph layouts, which is a topic in computer graphics and visualization. Therefore, cs.GR (Graphics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a neural network-based discriminator model, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the feature vectors used in the model are based on classical statistics and information-theoretical quantities, which are relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper uses methods from condensed matter physics to extract two-point statistics, which could be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
